00:37:46.500 --> 00:37:48.130
drop this and try something different."

00:37:48.130 --> 00:37:52.960
&gt;&gt;Chris: OK, good, so a couple different questions
there. I would say in terms of the feeling

00:37:52.960 --> 00:37:55.329
I get, and maybe you're asking what motivates
me, or what--

00:37:55.329 --> 00:37:56.329
&gt;&gt;audience #6: Yeah, yeah.

00:37:56.329 --> 00:38:01.069
&gt;&gt;Chris: Where do I find encouragement? I
would say the encouragement is mostly through

00:38:01.069 --> 00:38:05.380
the daily engagement with what I call the
small army of remarkable people. You know,

00:38:05.380 --> 00:38:11.420
so the people who are a part of the community,
both online and offline. So, every day I get

00:38:11.420 --> 00:38:15.410
a lot of emails, just like all of you do.
And many of the emails are people talking

00:38:15.410 --> 00:38:19.910
about sharing their own story and sharing
what they’re doing that's unconventional,

00:38:19.910 --> 00:38:23.730
different, and how they're overcoming pressure
and how our lives are connected. And I find

00:38:23.730 --> 00:38:30.240
that very motivating. I find that very encouraging
and as I said earlier, inspiring to me. Now

00:38:30.240 --> 00:38:36.869
as to what other should do, I mean, that's
a big, broad question. I guess I always think

00:38:36.869 --> 00:38:42.130
a couple of things. One, I think it’s very
difficult to do something on a long term basis

00:38:42.130 --> 00:38:48.340
that you're not motivated to do. I think it’s
much easier to do what you're motivated to

00:38:48.340 --> 00:38:52.480
do as opposed to trying to motivate yourself
into something. We all have things we have

00:38:52.480 --> 00:38:57.460
to do, like suck it up, get it done, but I
think if that's your career, then that's very

00:38:57.460 --> 00:39:03.220
difficult. So as much as possible, again,
for those of us in a relatively privileged

00:39:03.220 --> 00:39:09.940
setting, as much as possible, I think it’s
good to forge your life and your career around

00:39:09.940 --> 00:39:14.140
things that you're motivated to do and things
you're excited about. And in terms of blogging,

00:39:14.140 --> 00:39:18.340
whether you want to have a commercially successful
bog or just a blog that's popular or just

00:39:18.340 --> 00:39:23.520
a blog that a few people read, the question
to answer is always, "Why should other people

00:39:23.520 --> 00:39:27.920
care about this, and what's in it for them?"
And what are their needs and how are you providing

00:39:27.920 --> 00:39:32.981
a solution their needs? And if you do that,
then people will be interested in it. If not,

00:39:32.981 --> 00:39:36.869
probably not so much. And did you wanna have
a follow-up?

00:39:36.869 --> 00:39:41.369
&gt;&gt;audience #5: I just, you know, sorry. I
