00:40:10.550 --> 00:40:17.150
way, that makes sense and is appropriate,
not too fast, not too slow. But for the most

00:40:17.150 --> 00:40:21.490
part, I love what I do. I mean, I have a great
life. I'm very grateful. Thanks.

00:40:21.490 --> 00:40:28.500
&gt;&gt;Female audience #2: I'm Jen. I was wondering
if you have any advice on how to know when

00:40:28.500 --> 00:40:33.440
to let a project go and how to do so without
feeling guilty? I've been writing a blog for

00:40:33.440 --> 00:40:42.480
a few years and I have a few hundred followers.
I don't want to let them down, but I'm not

00:40:42.480 --> 00:40:47.240
gathering as much fulfillment from writing
the blog anymore. But I continue to do it

00:40:47.240 --> 00:40:48.559
out of not letting them down.

00:40:48.559 --> 00:40:51.940
&gt;&gt;Chris: You do it out of obligation?

00:40:51.940 --> 00:40:53.230
&gt;&gt;audience #2: Yeah.

00:40:53.230 --> 00:40:59.690
&gt;&gt;Chris: OK. Well, have you considered maybe
having a dialogue with those readers or followers

00:40:59.690 --> 00:41:04.520
and maybe just expressing your feelings? I
mean, this is something that's actually, blog

00:41:04.520 --> 00:41:11.069
readers respond very well to expressions of
your personal motivation and what you're feeling

00:41:11.069 --> 00:41:17.130
in terms of fulfillment. So, it’s almost
a kind of thing where if I felt that situation,

00:41:17.130 --> 00:41:22.020
I would try to think a bit myself and think,
"OK, why am I feeling this way? I was excited

00:41:22.020 --> 00:41:27.610
about this before, but something changed.
What changed? Is there a way that we can recreate

00:41:27.610 --> 00:41:31.100
what I had before, or is it just time to move
on and do something else?" And if that's the

00:41:31.100 --> 00:41:37.940
case, then that's fine. But it may also be
helpful to, instead of just focusing inwardly,

00:41:37.940 --> 00:41:43.260
one question that people always ask when you're
trying to figure out what to do, a lot of

00:41:43.260 --> 00:41:47.280
life coaches encourage people to ask themselves
the question, "What excites you?" So I think

00:41:47.280 --> 00:41:49.900
that's good. I think it's good, but I think
it's only a good start. So, I think you think

00:41:49.900 --> 00:41:54.380
about what excites you, but also what bothers
you. What bothers you about the world and

00:41:54.380 --> 00:41:58.240
so, that's a little bit more of an external
focus. So, in this case, maybe having a dialogue

00:41:58.240 --> 00:42:03.020
with the readers of the community, and just
sharing what you just shared and saying, “I

00:42:03.020 --> 00:42:05.290
was really excited about this for a while,
but now some things have changed in my life,

00:42:05.290 --> 00:42:10.599
or maybe I'm motivated by different things.
What do you think about that? And I think

00:42:10.599 --> 00:42:15.730
I might change the project entirely, or I
might start a new one, but let's have a conversation

00:42:15.730 --> 00:42:17.130
about it."

00:42:17.130 --> 00:42:24.619
&gt;&gt;Male audience #6: Hi, Chris. I'm wondering
what advice would you give for gaining the

00:42:24.619 --> 00:42:33.819
understanding of families in our pursuits
of nonconformity, or just motivation and happiness.

00:42:33.819 --> 00:42:41.560
I'm speaking particularly to living in a different
place, travelling abroad, what is a good balance

00:42:41.560 --> 00:42:47.140
and how do we achieve it between being happy
with our lives and getting other people to

00:42:47.140 --> 00:42:48.650
understand that we're happy with our lives?

00:42:48.650 --> 00:42:52.020
&gt;&gt;Chris: Right. That's a very good question.
And maybe we should actually end with this

00:42:52.020 --> 00:42:55.990
question and them I'm gonna hang out in the
back for anybody who wants to talk or sign

00:42:55.990 --> 00:43:00.820
a book. There's a number of things we could
say about that. I guess when we talk about

00:43:00.820 --> 00:43:05.720
resistance and pressure to conform it often
comes from family or close friends who don't

00:43:05.720 --> 00:43:11.410
understand why we want to do something. And
I think often, what is the case, especially

00:43:11.410 --> 00:43:15.720
in terms of travel or living somewhere else,
like you mentioned, I think there's a fear

00:43:15.720 --> 00:43:20.560
that you're gonna leave and never come back.
And so, sometimes it’s an irrational fear,

00:43:20.560 --> 00:43:25.120
or it’s a fear that something is going to
be different or changed. And so, sometimes

00:43:25.120 --> 00:43:29.650
it helps just to do something, or to go on
a trip or whatever and then you come back

00:43:29.650 --> 00:43:36.470
and the people say, "Oh, OK. He went away
and then he came back and he's still the person,

00:43:36.470 --> 00:43:41.110
the son, the brother, the husband, the partner,
or whoever, that I knew before." And so, I

00:43:41.110 --> 00:43:47.530
would say in many cases, people just get used
to things over time. If you spend your life

00:43:47.530 --> 00:43:52.560
trying to persuade them, trying to persuade
people to go along, you may be successful,

00:43:52.560 --> 00:43:58.020
but you could spend years doing that. Or,
you could just step out a little bit and then

00:43:58.020 --> 00:44:01.839
hopefully people will adjust. And often, that
fear comes out of, that resistance, comes

00:44:01.839 --> 00:44:06.400
out of fear and envy or jealousy. Or maybe
people wanna do something themselves, but

00:44:06.400 --> 00:44:11.430
they haven't been able to or they don't see
how they can do it. So, what's fun is by doing

00:44:11.430 --> 00:44:15.810
that, by actually stepping out and pursuing
whatever the unconventional choice is. In

00:44:15.810 --> 00:44:21.609
your case, what's fun is that you can then
be an inspiration to them. And they're not

00:44:21.609 --> 00:44:26.369
going to read books about nonconformity. They
don't read blogs, but they know you and your

00:44:26.369 --> 00:44:29.640
part of their lives. So, if you've done that,
then you're an inspiration and hopefully maybe

00:44:29.640 --> 00:44:37.839
they'll take a step as well. I could say a
lot more about that, but I think our time

00:44:37.839 --> 00:44:42.950
is up here, unless there's one more question.
